  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Spectral Analysis\n\nThis notebook explores frequency analysis of various signal types: chirps, amplitude-modulated signals, and square waves. We examine power spectral density, windowing effects, and the Gibbs phenomenon.\n\nAll FFT computations use `np_fft` / `np_ifft` with NumPy-compatible scaling conventions.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 145,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Chirp Signal (Frequency Sweep)\n\nA linear chirp sweeps from frequency $f_0$ to $f_1$ over duration $T$:\n\n$$x(t) = \\sin\\!\\left(2\\pi\\left(f_0 t + \\frac{f_1 - f_0}{2T}\\, t^2\\right)\\right)$$\n\nThe instantaneous frequency increases linearly from $f_0$ to $f_1$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate a chirp: 5 Hz to 60 Hz over 1 second */\nN : 1024$\nfs : 1024$\nt : np_scale(1.0/fs, np_arange(N))$\n\nf_start : 5$\nf_end : 60$\nT : 1.0$\n\n/* Phase: 2*pi*(f0*t + (f1-f0)/(2T) * t^2) */\nchirp_phase(ti) := 2 * float(%pi) * (f_start * ti + (f_end - f_start) / (2*T) * ti^2)$\nchirp : np_map(lambda([ti], sin(chirp_phase(ti))), t)$\n\nprint(\"Chirp signal:\", f_start, \"Hz to\", f_end, \"Hz\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 146,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Chirp signal: 5 Hz to 60 Hz"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot chirp waveform */\nt_list : np_to_list(t)$\nchirp_list : np_to_list(chirp)$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"teal\", line_width=1.5,\n  lines(t_list, chirp_list),\n  title=\"Linear Chirp (5-60 Hz)\",\n  xlabel=\"Time (s)\", ylabel=\"Amplitude\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 147,
      "outputs": [
        {
